2). DTO(Data transfer object)

    DTO are simple java class that represent the subset of entity model that can have more
    information.These are designed to tranfer data between service and component

3). What actually happening

    Entity stores actual database data.
    Request DTO takes input.
    Response DTO sends output.
    Data is converted between DTO and Entity.

    DTO is just like a wrapper/filter for transferring data safely and cleanly.

4).How it is done

    DTO Flow (Category Example)

    User sends data → Request DTO form
    Request DTO converted to → Entity pass in → Database
    from Database → Entity  is retreived as → Response DTO and it is passed to → User

    How it works
    Controller receives Request DTO
    Service converts DTO → Entity and saves in DB
    Service converts Entity → Response DTO
    Controller returns Response DTO to user

5).for converting this to category to  request DTO , request DTO to category ,
    category to response DTO we need Modelmapper
    Add ModelMapper dependencies in your project and a bean of this modelmapper.as there is no separate
    class present for this create bean in appconfig class and mark that class as configuration class. wherever
    needed Retreive that modelmapper and  use this to convert.
    modelmapper.map(category,CategoroyDTO.class)


     this technique give better control what input to take and what to show to user

Now we have understand how data should be taken , data to be store, data to be shown to user
Now Next concept is :

6).Pagination

    Pagination means dividing large data into small pages and showing one page at a time.

    🧠 Simple Example

    Instead of showing 1000 customers at once:

    Page 1 → 10 customers
    Page 2 → next 10 customers
    Page 3 → next 10 customers

    for this

    we use Pageable interface and PageRequest clas which implement this Pageable interface

    PageNumber,PageSize Take this two parameter as input using requestparam

    Pageable PageDetails = PageRequest.of(PageNumber,PageSize);
    Page<Category> categoryPage = categoryRepository.findAll(PageDetails);

    List<Category> categories = categoryPage.getContent();
    HERE Page contain a list of object
    Here PageNumber means in which page should you want to go like page means a bunch of customer
    PageSize means = no. of customer in one page
    Along with that we have to create some other variable too

            private Integer pageNumber;
            private Integer pageSize;
            private Long totalElement;
            private Integer totalPages;
            private boolean lastPage;

    these all should be define in CategoryResponse for output
    this all information when we return along with data then it is actually pagination in action


6).AppConstant

    It is a class which is used for defining all constant varibale at one place
    for Ex. pageNumber,PageSize we want default value for these varible too
            so such information is stored here so to change we can get all
            constant variable at one place

7).Sorting

    It is a way of arranging data on various parameter
    for this
        Sort sortByAndOrder = sortOrder.equalsIgnoreCase("asc") ?
                        Sort.by(sortBy).ascending()
                        : Sort.by(sortBy).descending();
    Again we have to take every parameter on the basis of you want
    to arrange  in ascending or descending order
    Ex. in our project we have two thing categoryId and CategoryName
    and we want to arrange data on basis of any parameter
    so We take both parameter as RequestParam and need to provide
    default value to as at one time we don't want to arrange data on all
    parameter basis or default value in necessary
    Then in serviceImpl we have to use Sort to define sorting way
8).Standard Exception Returning
    Using APIResponse: use to send standart format for exception
    ex.
    {
        "message": "Category not found with CategoryId:1",
        "status": false
    }
    In  such form so use this class and wherever we want to send Exception
    we pass message and status to this class

